!!! html
%html
  %head
    = Haml::Engine.new(File.read("assets/haml-includes/head.haml")).render

  %body
    = Haml::Engine.new(File.read("assets/haml-includes/navigation.haml")).render

    %div{:class => 'community-logo'}
    %div{:class => 'site-content'}
      %div{:class => 'how-to is-typeset'}
        %div{:class => 'row-parent'}
          %div{:class => 'row'}
            %section{:class => 'row__colspaced'}
              %div{:class => 'colspan12-8 push12-2 colspan8-8 colspan6-6 colspan2-1 as-grid with-gutter'}
                %div{:class => 'col__module--cta'}
                  %h2 Community

        %div{:class => 'row-parent'}
          %div{:class => 'row'}
            %section{:class => 'row__colspaced'}
              %div{:class => 'colspan12-8 push12-2 colspan8-8 colspan6-6 colspan2-1 as-grid with-gutter'}
                %div{:class => 'col__module--img'}
                  %p
                    We welcome your involvement in the Performance Co-Pilot project!
                    If you have discovered a bug, or wish to see a specific new feature, please report that in our issue tracking system.
                  %p
                    We are greatly interested in any efforts to expand the scope
                    of the available performance metrics with new plugins or
                    agents, to port existing performance tools to the PCP APIs,
                    and to develop new clients to consume and display
                    performance data delivered over the PCP APIs.
                  %p
                    If you are interested in getting involved in any of these areas we
                    recommend joining the PCP mailing list, the pcp IRC channel,
                    writing new code, and sending your changes out early for review.
                  %p
                    Please refer to the 
                    %a{:href => "https://github.com/performancecopilot/pcp/blob/master/HACKING"} HACKING
                    file in the top level of the
                    PCP source tree for further information about getting
                    involved. Please read the 
                    %a{:href => "/faq.html"} FAQ
                    before posting on the mailing lists.

        %div{:class => 'row-parent'}
          %div{:class => 'row'}
            %section{:class => 'row__colspaced'}
              %div{:class => 'colspan12-4 colspan8-3 colspan6-2 colspan2-2 as-grid with-gutter'}
                %div{:class => 'col__module--img'}
                  %h3 Mailing lists
                  %p
                    Patches, comments, requests and questions should go to:
                    %br
                    %a{:href => 'mailto:pcp@oss.sgi.com'} pcp@oss.sgi.com
                  %p
                    Announcements of new releases and PCP presentations:
                    %br
                    %a{:href => 'mailto:pcp-announce@oss.sgi.com'} pcp-announce@oss.sgi.com
                  %h4 Subscribe
                  %p 
                    Subscribe to the mailing lists using one of the web interfaces at:
                    %ul
                      %li
                        %a{:href => 'http://www.pcp.io/mailman/listinfo/pcp'} pcp
                      %li
                        %a{:href => 'http://www.pcp.io/mailman/listinfo/pcp-announce'} pcp-announce

                  %h4 Archives
                  %p
                    The list archives can be found here:
                    %ul
                      %li
                        %a{:href => 'http://www.pcp.io/pipermail/pcp'} pcp
                      %li
                        %a{:href => 'http://www.pcp.io/pipermail/pcp-announce'} pcp-announce
                   
              %div{:class => 'colspan12-4 colspan8-3 colspan6-2 colspan2-2 as-grid with-gutter'}
                %div{:class => 'col__module--img'}
                  %h3 IRC
                  %p
                    You can also chat directly with some of the PCP developers, on the #pcp IRC channel on the
                    %a{:href => 'https://freenode.net/'}FreeNode
                    network.
                  %p
                    Use your favourite IRC client or try Freenode's 
                    %a{:href => 'https://webchat.freenode.net/'} web interface

              %div{:class => 'colspan12-4 colspan8-3 colspan6-2 colspan2-2 as-grid with-gutter'}
                %div{:class => 'col__module--img'}
                  %h3 Social
                  %p
                    %ul
                      %li
                        %a{:href => 'https://twitter.com/performancepcp'} Twitter
                      %li
                        %a{:href => 'https://github.com/performancecopilot'} Github

              %div{:class => 'colspan12-8 colspan8-5 colspan6-3 colspan2-2 as-grid with-gutter'}
                %div{:class => 'col__module--img'}
                  %br
                  %br
                  %h3 Easy hacks
                  %p
                    Here is a list of bugs that are easy to fix. Start contributing today:
                    %br
                    %a{:href => '/easyhacks.html'} Easy Hacks

              %div{:class => 'colspan12-8 colspan8-5 colspan6-3 colspan2-2 as-grid with-gutter'}
                %div{:class => 'col__module--img'}
                  %br
                  %br
                  %h3 BuildBot
                  %p
                    Help ensure PCP functions perfectly on your favourite platform!
                    %br
                    %a{:href => 'http://buildbot.pcp.io'} BuildBot Web Interface
                    %br
                    %a{:href => '/buildbot.html'} Contribute a BuildBot

    = Haml::Engine.new(File.read("assets/haml-includes/footer.haml")).render
